  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-04-29",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Fairness for America's Heroes Act - Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to: (1) extend automatic naturalization (upon commencement of combat service) to a noncitizen member of the armed forces who serves on active service below the grade of commissioned officer in a combat zone; and (2) provide immigration benefits to the spouse, child, or parent of a member of the armed forces who was granted posthumous citizenship through death while on active duty service during a period of military hostilities."
  },
